                                @{b}REGISTRATION@{ub}
                            ====================


With version V2.0 StartupControl is released as @{FG shine}SHAREWARE@{FG text}. You are allowed to
test this program for 14 days. If you want to use it later on you have to pay
the  shareware fee to ADSG.  I think the  requested fee is  not that much, so
even "poor  students" can afford  to pay it.  It will help  and spur me on to
improve StartupControl in the future.

           @{FG shine}··· a program worth using is a program worth buying ···@{FG text}

               Shareware fee is: 20DM (for email registration)
                                 25DM (for mail registration)

                    Please use the included register-tool.

@{b}Registration of  StartupControl is done by  ADSG. You tranfer your  shareware
fee to  ADSG`s account  or  send cash  via  mail. You will get  your personal
keyfile and the latest version of StartupControl.

 further information on ADSG`s homepage at @{FG shine}www.amigaworld.com/adsg@{FG text}
@{ub}

The keyfile allows you to use this and all coming versions of StartupControl.
Updates will be  released on  Aminet as until now. You can  download, install
and use them without any further requests.

When your personal keyfile has arrived from ADSG, copy it to your S: drawer.
When you start StartupControl next time you can read your name in the about-
window and the registration-requester will not pop up anymore.



@endnode

@node "Changes" "Introduction"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Registration"

                          @{b}Changes in version 2.01a@{ub}
                      ================================


Along with version 2.01a come some changes in installation and handling
of StartupControl.

    1. From now on the assign ENV: to ENVARC: is done by StartupControl
       automaticly. A second assign T: to RAM: os done too, to allow
       the improvements in the startup-option.
       These assigns will also be done in your original startup-sequence
       some lines after StartupControl and will be set to its standard-
       directories (RAM:ENV and RAM:T)

       @{b}REMOVE "assign ENV: ENVARC:" from your startup-sequence! Its no
       longer needed.
@{ub}
    2. Commandline-options are no longer used. All options can be set,
       changed and saved in the new preferences-window.

    3. With version 2.01a StartupControl is @{FG shine}SHAREWARE@{FG text}. Its free 14 days
       for testing.

@{b}Please read the documentation carfully. Almost every feature has been
improved.
@{ub}
@endnode

@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Changes"

                              @{b}INTRODUCTION@{ub}
                          ====================


@{b}PLEASE READ THIS DOCUMENTATION CAREFULLY BEFORE USING STARTUPCONTROL FOR THE
FIRST TIME TO UNDERSTAND HOW THE PROGRAM WORKS!@{ub}

StartupControl is a  "multifunctional utility"  for your Startup-Sequence.
It was designed with the  intention  to offer direct control to  the boot-
process combined with easiest operation and much comfort.
With StartupControl you  can  get  information  about the status  of  your
computer and set a desired configuration every time your Amiga boots.

Comparable tools mostly  offer only  one out of StartupControls options or
are very  specific  to a single  topic and  overloaded  with  features and
therefore not easy to use.

StartupControl tries to close this gap and offer useful features which are
easy to use.

If you have any comments,  suggestions, ideas or  bug reports, please mail
the @{"author" link Author}.


                                                                Dirk Jesse

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Introduction"

                             @{b}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}
                         ====================


    You need following to use StartupControl:

        o any Amiga with installed OS2.04 (V37) or higher

        o installed AmigaDos commands: execute, lock, assign
          (the "run" and "newshell" command are in ROM since OS2.04)

          @{FG shine}WARNING: StartupControl doesn`t look for these commands.
                   If they aren`t installed, some features probably
                   will not work correctly !
@{FG text}

        o reqtools.library, if you want to use reqtools-filerequester

        o Workbench 2.1 or better for using PAL-Option

        @{b}o registered users have to copy their keyfile to S: directroy !
@{ub}
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Requirements"

                                @{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}
                            ====================

Starting with V2.22, StartupControl can be installed with the installer. You
should do it  this way.  Anyway here  still is the procedure  to install the
program yourself:

    o As StartupControl is a simple command I recommend to copy it to
      your "C:" directory.

    o Insert the following line into your startup-sequence @{b}after@{ub} the
      SetPatch-command:

      "<path>StartupControl".

    o As I remember - that`s all...




@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "History"
@prev "Installation"

                                 @{b}USAGE@{ub}
                             =============


First thing, StartupControl  does  when it`s executed, is to check  if all
existing  Volumes are  @{"validated." link "validation" 0} If StartupControl  finds a drive that`s
under validating it will wait and check this drive once a second until its
valitated, while a nice  Infobox  will inform you about what happens.
After this StartupControl takes a  look at the @{"systemtime" link Systemzeit}. If the battery-
clock has crashed it opens a  window where you can  easily set actual date
and time.

When StartupControl is installed correctly, it is easy to use. Simply hold
down  @{b}@{FG shine}left or right ALT key@{FG text}@{ub} or press the @{b}@{FG shine}left mousebutton@{FG text}@{ub} after a reset or
after  switching  on  your  machine  and  StartupControl  will open a nice
window offering a variety of functions.

