@node "Systemzeit" "Systemtime Check"
@next "CacheControl"
@prev "Usage"

                              @{b}Systemtime Check@{ub}
                          ========================


Some gurus of our amiga lead to crash of the batteryclock. If that happens the
date is set to 01.01.1978.
StartupControl saves  the systemtime every  bootup. At next bootup it compares
this time with the actual  systemtime. If it isn`t "later" in time there must
be an error. Then StartupControl opens a window where you can easily edit date
and time.

This option must be activated in the @{"preferences" link Preferences 100} window.


@endnode

@node "CacheControl" "Cache Control"
@next "WB+User"
@prev "Systemzeit"

                              @{b}Cache Control@{ub}
                          =====================
With this feature you can control cache, burst and copyback modes of your
processor. Please note that @{b}Burst Modes@{ub} are only  available with at least
an 68030 and @{b}Copyback@{ub} with a 68040 processor.

To make the cache settings durable, you have to save your settings in the
@{"preferences" link Preferences 100} window.


@endnode
@node "WB+User" "WB+User"
@next "Assigns"
@prev "CacheControl"
@{b}WB Options@{ub}

      @{b}WB+User@{ub}   -> disables both, WBStartup and User-Startup and
                   continues startup-sequence

      @{b}WB@{ub}        -> only disables WBStartup and continues startup-sequence

      @{b}User@{ub}      -> only disables User-Startup and continues startup-sequence
@endnode



@node "Assigns" "Assign Preferences"
@next "Last Alert"
@prev "WB+User"

    _________________________________________________________________
   | StartupControl V2.33 · Assign Preferences                       |
   | _______________________________________________________________ |
   ||ADPro    LATE -> Harddisk:Grafik/ADPro                         ||
   || ...                                                           ||
   || ...                                                           ||
   || ...                                                           ||
   ||                                                               ||
   ||                                                               ||
   ||                                                               ||
   ||                                                               ||
   ||_______________________________________________________________||
   |                                                                 |
   |  Add       Remove      System       Up  Down              Sort  |
   |                                                                 |
   |  xxxxxxxxxx  ->  xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx     AssignType  |
   |                                                                 |
   |                                                                 |
   |  Save                                      Use          Cancel  |
   |_________________________________________________________________|


Now, it`s possible to do all  nesseccary assigns from  Startup-Sequence and
User-Startup with StartupControl and remove them from the scripts.

The new  Assign-Preferences work  allmost like MCP or  AssignManager. It is
posssible to use the  entries from MCP.config by  copying the ASCII-entries
to StartupControl`s AssignPrefs-file.


    @{FG shine}Add@{FG text}        Add a new Assign to the list. In the left Textfield you must
               insert the name of the assigns (@{b}without colon@{ub}). In the right
               Textfield, there  you have to  inseert  the path,  where the
               assign points to.

    @{FG shine}AssignType@{FG text} With tihs  cyclegadget the  type of  the assign  can be set.
               Following types are possible:

               @{b}LATE@{ub} - the assign gets active, when you use it for the first
                      time.
                      (You should  use this type  especially  for  program-
                      assigns. As  long  the assign  is not  used,  it wont
                      appear in any filerequester.)

               @{b}PATH@{ub} - simple assign with name and drawer

               @{b}LOCK@{ub} - protected assign:  the path  of this  assign  will be
                      protected by a Doslock  and the drawer (+ subdrawers)
                      can`t be deleted.

               @{b}ADD@{ub}  - the new  assign will  be added to an existing assign.
                      The existing one has to be from type LOCK.

    @{FG shine}Remove@{FG text}     removes a selected assign from the list

    @{FG shine}System@{FG text}     add an already existing assign to the list

    @{FG shine}Sort@{FG text}       listentries become sorted...

All assigns from the list will be saved to S:SC2_Assigns.prefs as an ASCII-
file.

@{FG shine}@{b}If you change prefs manually, don`t change fileformat !!@{ub}
@{FG text}

@endnode
@node "Last Alert" "Last Alert"
@next "Logfile"
@prev "Assigns"
          ___________________________________________________________
         |StartupControl V2.33 · Last Alert Information              |
         |   _____________________________________________________   |
         |  |                                                     |  |
         |  |               ··· Last Alert Info ···               |  |
         |  |                                                     |  |
         |  |             Number :  $xxxxxx                       |  |
         |  |                                                     |  |
         |  |             Name   :  xxxxxxxxxxxxxxx               |  |
         |  |             Address:  $xxxxxx                       |  |
         |  |                                                     |  |
         |  |             Cause  :  xxxxxxxx                      |  |
         |  |             Object :  xxxxxxxx                      |  |
         |  |             Descr. :  xxxxxxxx                      |  |
         |  |_____________________________________________________|  |
         |                                                           |
         |  @{"Save to logfile" link Logfile}                                @{"Go back" link "Usage" 0}  |
         |___________________________________________________________|

This requester gives you detailed information about the last alert. If
possible the name of the task that caused the alert is displayed.

StartupControl tries to find out which task caused the alert. It looks for the
task-name in memory. Because memory isn`t cleared during reset in many cases
StartupControl finds  the name. If the task-structure is destroyed in any way,
the name is not available ...sorry, that`s life!
@endnode

