@endnode

@node "Startup" "Startup"
@next "SysInfo"
@prev "Exe"
@{b}Startup - Button@{ub}

      @{b}Startup@{ub}   -> opens a filerequester where you can select an
                   alternative startup-sequence to execute. It doesn`t
                   go back to the menu after execution.

If you often use this option, you should set the @{b}"Startfiles flag"@{ub} in the
@{"Preferences" link "Preferences" 56} window. Read the explanation there for further information on how
to use this feature.

Without the @{b}Startupfiles@{ub}, StartupControl does the following:

StartupControl runs the scriptfile via "Execute" command and than leans back,
falls into sleep and waits for a never comming Signal. So the old
startup-sequence is stopped and won`t be continued. As long as you don`t use a
systemmonitor you will not realize that StartupControl is still in memory.

This methode is acceptable if you hardly use this option and you don`t have to
change and rename your original startup-sequence.
@endnode

