       |  |_______________________________________________________|  |
       |                                                             |
       |   @{"ColdReboot" link "ColdReboot" 0}           @{"Clear Vectors" link "Clear Vectors" 0}            @{"Go back" link "Usage" 0}   |
       |_____________________________________________________________|


This option has been improved in V2.20.  It shows the most important resetvec-
tors of the system. This should be useful for both, developer and user.

Using the @{b}capture-vectors@{ub} or  @{b}KickTagPtr@{ub} programs can survive a reset. Several
programs and patches use this way to become "reset-proof" but also viruses are
possible users of these vectors.
StartupControl reads the  content of these vectors and informs you if they are
not empty  (NULL). StartupControl  can`t  find out  eigther these entries  are
friendy or a possible virus.

Below the satus of @{"validation" link Validation}-tested drives is displayed. If a drive couldn`t
be validated, a message will be displayed.

The last two lines contain the @{"systemtime" link Systemzeit} and batteryclock time. StartupControl
takes a look at the systemtime every  bootup if you activate the option in the
@{"preferences" link Preferences 100} window.


@endnode

@node "(Un)Lock" "(Un)Lock"
@next "PAL"
@prev "SysInfo"
@{b}(Un)Lock - Button@{ub}

      @{b}(Un)Lock@{ub}  -> gives you the opportunity to make selected devices
                   @{b}WRITE-DISABLED@{ub}. So you can forbid any write-access
                   to  your  harddrives. A further selection  of this
                   gadget removes the lock from the drives.

      @{b}Lock at exit@{ub}  is useful, when you want to protect your drives, but also
                    want to use WB- or PAL-option. StartupControl will process
                    these options first before it protects your drives.
                    (Because WB- and PAL-option need write access to HD, your
                    drives should be not protected at this time.)

To use this option you have to activate the button in the @{"preferences" link Preferences 44} window
and to tell StartupControl the names of all drives you want to protect.

@endnode

@node "PAL" "PAL"
@next "ColdReboot"
@prev "(Un)Lock"
                            @{b}Force PAL Workbench@{ub}
                            -------------------

This  part  of  StartupControl  was  completely  rewritten  in V2.11.  Now
"screenmode.prefs" from  Workbench  will be  patched  directly.  With this
change,  now it`s possible to freely  select resolution  and depth of  the
PAL screen in the @{"preferences" link Preferences} window.
As before the monitordrivers  from DEVS:Monitors will be disabled to load.

@{FG shine}                                                    !! OS2.1+ is needed !!@{FG text}

@endnode

@node "ColdReboot" "ColdReboot"
@next "Clear Vectors"
@prev "PAL"
@{b}ColdReboot - Button@{ub}

      @{b}ColdReboot@{ub} -> This routine clears the @{b}capture-vectors@{ub} and the
                    @{b}KickTagPtr@{ub}. Then it does a cold reboot of your dream-machine.
                    You will get a clear system after reboot.
@endnode

@node "Clear Vectors" "Clear Vectors"
@next ""
@prev "ColdReboot"
@{b}Clear Vectors - Button@{ub}

      @{b}Clear Vectors@{ub} -> This clears the @{b}capture-vectors@{ub} and the
                       @{b}KickTagPtr@{ub}. No reset will be done.
                       -> You will get a clear system after next reboot.
@endnode

@node "Exit" "Exit"
@next ""
@prev "Usage"
@{b}Exit - Button@{ub}

      @{b}Exit@{ub}    -> Use it to leave StartpControl. The settings for
                 PAL, WB and Lock options will be executed.


                 If you want to leave StartupControl without using any of
                 this settings (useful only if you changed them after popup)
                 you have to exit by pressing the Close-Gadget of the window.
@endnode

@node "Validation" "Validation"
@next ""
@prev "Usage"

                          @{b}"Disk xxx not validated"@{ub}
                      ================================


Oh, what an oawfull message in those days of Workbench 1.3 ... but those days
are  gone  and  we  all have at least  WB2.04.  Never the less the
validation-problem is still present sometimes.

When files  are written to e.g. your harddisk  then some free  blocks on disk
get filled with data.  There is a  bitmap  on disk where all filled blocks are
signed in.  When a file is written  completely to disk, this bitmap is
updated. But  sometimes a lousy  bastard called "total system hang up" (GURU
in short) appears and a saving process can`t be finished. When this happens
there are filled  blocks on disk that aren`t signed in the disks bitmap ->
Disk is not validated!

With WB2.04 this  will be repaired automaticly but it mostly comes along with
a system boot and they obstruct themselves  each  other. That`s why
StartupControl recognises this and stops booting for a while, until disk is
repaired.

When everything has turned into sunshine, your Amiga will boot as always.

@endnode

@node "History" "History"
@next "Problems"
@prev "Usage"

                                 @{b}HISTORY@{ub}
                             ===============


@{b}V2.33 (15.Sep.98) MINOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o Easy PAL    : When Pal-option is activated, only Workbench Screen
                    will be patchec to PAL. Monitordrivers will be loaded,
                    so you can switch to other resolutions later.
    o RegTool     : There is a new version of ADSG`s RegTool included.
                    This should make on problems anymore.


@{b}V2.30 (18.November.97) MAJOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o @{b}BUG REMOVED @{ub}: When Pal-option was activated, StartupControl didn`t execute
                    an alternative startup-sequence anymore.
    o @{"Force Popup " link Preferences 100}: Forces StartupControl to open its gui
    o NEW KEYFILE : All registerd users of StartupControl will get thier new
                    keyfile from ADSG within the next two weeks.


@{b}V2.22 (23.October.97) MINOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o @{"Countdown" link Preferences 110} Option: StartupControl will wait an amount of seconds for
      activation, before startup-sequence is continued.
    o several internal changes


@{b}V2.21 (09.October.97) MINOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o @{b}BUG REMOVED  : @{ub}ADD-Assigns were not installed correctly, so
                     the machine could even crash !!
    o AssignManager: you can add now existing systemassigns to the list
    o @{"CacheControl" link CacheControl} allows you to set Cache, Burst and Copyback modes
    o Preferences window rearanged
    o Clockcheck got "Get last saved" button.


@{b}V2.20 (27.September.97) MAJOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o Now StartupControl watches the @{"Batteryclock" link Systemzeit}. If the clock has
      crashed, you can edit date and time in a window. This option can
      be activated in the @{"Preferences" link Preferences 100} window.
    o The "Vectors" option was renamed to @{"System Info" link SysInfo} and improved.
      Now you also get drive- and clock-informationen.


@{b}V2.12  (19.September.97) MINOR UPDATE@{ub}
    @{b}BUG REMOVED:@{ub} StartupControl didn`t load "ADD"-type assigns from
                 prefsfile !!


@{b}V2.11  (15.September.97) MAJOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o Assign-Manager integrated. This manager makes, if you want,
      all assigns from Startup-Sequence and User-Startup
    o PAL-Option completely rewritten. Now you can choose
      resolution and depth of your PAL screen.
    o PAL-Option now reacts with a visible warning, if the PAL patch
      couldn`t be installed.


@{b}V2.02  (06.September.97) MINOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o LastAlert-Info can be saved to a logfile, if you want.
      Name and path of this logfile can be set in the preferences
      window.
    o !! format of prefsfiles has changed !!
      To allow easier changes in the prefsfile, when adding new options,
      I changed the prefs-format.
    o standards for shell-window and logfile included, if no prefsfile
      exists.


@{b}V2.01a  (20.Juni.97)  MAJOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o Last Alert Info added
    o Validationcheck improved
    o Shell option improved
    o Lock option improved
    o new comfortable GUI added » made with GadToolsBox V2.0b
    o Preferences editor added
    o several code clean up`s
    o Startup option improved
    o About + Help window added
    o Keyboard control added
    o Keyfile-Support added
    o German Guide added

    (23.Juni.97)
    o StartupControl can be canceled via Escape
    o Gadget will be disabled on "Exit"

    - Error in Registration-info removed
    - Bug removed: StartupControl didn`t "Exit" if no Prefs
                   were saved.
    - Bug removed: StartupControl did wait 2 instead of 1 sec. if PAL-
                   and WB-option were used.


@{b}V1.4  (21.Apr.97) !! no public release !!@{ub}
    o Validationcheck added
    o removed "bugs" in documentation


@{b}V1.3  (11.Nov.96)  MAJOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o Startup-Option added
    o Vectors-Option added (System-Guru V1.0 included)
    o (Un)Lock-Option added
    o splitted up GUI to make all these new options possible
    o Code improved + cleaned up + sometimes rewritten
      (I hope I didn`t add a bug again!)
    o arranged Userguide in a better way


@{b}V1.2  (29.Oct.96)  MINOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o Bug removed: In some cases StartupControl used wrong a path and
      didn`t find files !
      (I tried to do this option really safe but reached the oposite...
      ...that`s life!)
      Bug found & reported by B. Breuer

@{b}V1.1  (23.May.96)  MINOR UPDATE@{ub}
    o EXE-Option added
    o after SCRIPT- and EXE-Option, StartupControl returns to its menu
      to allow further selections
    o there are no longer two versions for OS2.0 and OS2.1+ (two in one!)
    o ReqTools Support and commandline-option added
    o StartupControl sets CurrentDir to ProgDir to help programs to find
      their stuff
    o minor code changes

@{b}V1.0  (11.Juni.95)@{ub}
    o first public release




@endnode

@node "Problems" "That causes sleeples nights"
@prev "History"
@next "Author"
                           @{b}known problems@{ub}
                       ======================


There are some  programs that cause problems  when using StartupControl.


    @{b}Speedup@{ub}             Speedup  installs  itself  when  you  start   it
                        for the  first  time and  afterwards it  does  a
                        reset. It doesn`t  wait until  disk-activity has
                        finished  and  so  it   sometimes  causes  "non-
                        validated" disks.
                        Since V2.01a StartupControl waits a second after
                        every write-access to avoid this problem.

    @{b}FastIPrefs V40.36b@{ub}  After  StartupControl  poped up,  the  workbench
                        didn`t start correctly.  This error occours only
                        when  if  this   betaversion  of  FastIPrefs  is
                        installed.
                        I can`t explain this problem  - I use FastIPrefs
                        V40.12 without any problems !

    @{b}NewReqLibs@{ub}          This packet  patches REQ-  and  ASL-Library. The
                        standard libs are replaced by much shorter files.
                        But  the patched version of ASL-library  doesn`t
                        find  ENV: although  it was set  correctly. This
                        problem causes a requester every boot process.



@endnode

